<big><big>When we don't want to updata application program,</big></big> <br />
<big><big>the bootloader program should run to application program.</big></big><br />
<big><big>In order to achieve this goal, we can add under code in your bootloader program.</big></big><br />

<font color="red" size="4">asm volatile("ldr r0, =0x4000");</font> <font color="blue">//"the 0x4000 is my application program's MSP point, you must change it adapt to your"</font>   <br />
<font color="red" size="4">asm volatile("ldr r0, [[r0]]");</font><br />
<font color="red" size="4">asm volatile("mov sp, r0");</font><br />
	
<font color="red" size="4">asm volatile("ldr r0, =0x4004");</font> <font color="blue">//"the 0x4004 is my application program reset-function entry address, you must change it adapt to your"</font><br />
<font color="red" size="4">asm volatile("ldr r0, [[r0]]");</font><br />
<font color="red" size="4">asm volatile("mov pc, r0");</font><br />
